/*!
\page array_num2str NUM2STR Convert Numbers To Strings

<p>
Section: \ref sec_array "Array Generation and Manipulations"
\section Usage
Converts an array into its string representation.  The general syntax
for this function is
\verbatim
   s = num2str(X)
\endverbatim
where <tt>s</tt> is a string (or string matrix) and <tt>X</tt> is an array.  By
default, the <tt>num2str</tt> function uses 4 digits of precision and an 
exponent if required.  If you want more digits of precision, you can 
specify the precition via the form
\verbatim
   s = num2str(X, precision)
\endverbatim
where <tt>precision</tt> is the number of digits to include in the string
representation.  For more control over the format of the output, you 
can also specify a format specifier (see <tt>printf</tt> for more details).
\verbatim
   s = num2str(X, format)
\endverbatim
where <tt>format</tt> is the specifier string.
*/
